{{der-top|Compounds}}
* {{ja-r|丹%桂|たん%けい|golden osmanthus (''[[Osmanthus fragrans]]'')}}
* {{ja-r|桂%子|^けい%こ}}: a female given name
* {{ja-r|桂%飴|かつら%あめ}}: a type of [[sweet]] traditionally sold in villages in the mountains around Kyōto Prefecture
* {{ja-r|桂%鮎|かつら%あゆ}}: [[ayu]] ([[sweetfish]]) caught in the Katsura River in Kyōto
* {{ja-r|桂%庵|けい%あん}}: a [[mediary]] in an arranged marriage or in a [[lawsuit]]; a hiring [[placement]] specialist
* {{ja-r|桂%園|^けい%えん}}: [[pseudonym]] for {{m|ja|香川景樹|tr=Kagawa Kageki}}, a poet during the late {{w|Edo Period}}
* {{ja-r|桂%園%一%枝|^けい%えん %^いっ%し}}: a private [[anthology]] of poetry printed towards the end of the {{w|Edo Period}}
* {{ja-r|桂%園%派|^けい%えん%は}}: a style of {{m|ja|和歌|tr=waka}} poetry, founded by {{m|ja|香川景樹|tr=Kagawa Kageki}}
* {{ja-r|桂%科|かつら%か}}: the [[Cercidiphyllaceae]] [[family]], containing only the ''[[Cercidiphyllum]]'' [[genus]], containing only the two [[species]] ''[[Cercidiphyllum japonicum]]'' and {{taxlink|Cercidiphyllum magnificum|species|noshow=1}}, both commonly called {{m|ja|桂|tr=katsura}}
* {{ja-r|桂%花|けい%か}}, {{ja-r|桂華|けいか}}: {{qualifier|metaphor}} the [[moon]], from a Chinese legend of trees growing on the moon
* {{ja-r|桂%冠|けい%かん}}: a [[laurel]] [[wreath]]
* {{ja-r|桂%冠%詩%人|けい%かん% し%じん}}: a [[poet]] [[laureate]]
* {{ja-r|桂%巻|かつら% まき}}: a style of women's head wrapping popular during the {{w|Muromachi Period}}, using a long piece of cloth tied in front above the forehead
* {{ja-r|桂宮|^かつら-の-みや}}: one of the four {{m|ja|親王家|tr=shinnōke||branches of the Imperial Family of Japan which were eligible to succeed to the Chrysanthemum Throne in the event that the main line should die out}}
* {{ja-r|桂%宮%院|^けい%きゅう%いん}}, {{ja-r|桂%宮%院|^けい%ぐう%いん}}: the inner temple building at the {{w|Hōryū-ji|Hōryūji Temple}} in Kyoto
* {{ja-r|桂%月|けい%げつ}}: alternate word for {{m|ja|月|tr=tsuki||the moon}}; the eighth [[lunar month]]
* {{ja-r|桂%湖%村|^かつら% ^こ%そん}}: a Japanese author, lived 1868-1934
* {{ja-r|桂%江|^けい%こう}}: a river in the Chūgoku region of Japan
* {{ja-r|桂%三%木%助|^かつら% ^み%き%すけ}}: a traditional Japanese comedian ({{m|ja|落語|tr=rakugo}} performer); the first by this name lived 1894-1943, the second lived 1902-1961
* {{ja-r|桂%枝|けい%し}}: a [[branch]] from a [[cassia]], [[katsura]], [[laurel]], or [[cinnamon]] tree; a branch from the [[legendary]] tree that grows on the [[moon]]
* {{ja-r|桂%芝|けい%し}}: alternate word for {{m|ja|万年茸|tr=mannentake}}, a type of [[mushroom]]
* {{ja-r|桂%樹|けい%じゅ}}: common name for various trees in [[family]] [[Lauraceae]], particularly the [[cinnamon]] or [[cassia]] trees; a legendary tree growing on the moon; alternate for {{m|ja|浜枇杷|tr=hamabiwa||a type of tree in the genus {{taxlink|Litsea|genus|noshow=1}}, related to the [[laurel]]}}
* {{ja-r|桂%秋|けい%しゅう}}: alternate word for {{m|ja|秋|tr=aki||autumn}}
* {{ja-r|桂%春%団%治|^かつら% ^はる%だん%じ}}: [[stage name]] for {{m|ja|川田藤吉|tr=Kawada Fujiyoshi}}, a {{m|ja|落語|tr=rakugo||traditional Japanese comedy}} performer in [[Ōsaka]], lived 1881-1937
* {{ja-r|桂%女|かつら%め}}: a type of {{m|ja|巫女|tr=miko||shrine maiden}}; a woman selling of ''katsura ayu'' and ''katsura ame'' in areas around old Kyōto; a [[prostitute]] from the village of Katsura near Kyōto; a [[noblewoman]]'s [[bridesmaid]] in ancient Japan
* {{ja-r|桂%小%五%郎|^かつら% ^こ%ご%ろう}}: former name of {{m|ja|木戸孝允|tr={{w|Kido Takayoshi}}}}, an important [[politician]] in the late {{w|Edo Period}} and early {{w|Meiji Period}}
* {{ja-r|桂%昌%院|^けい%しょう%いん}}: [[concubine]] of {{m|ja|徳川家光|tr={{w|Tokugawa Iemitsu}}}}, the third Tokugawa [[shōgun]]
* {{ja-r|桂%心|けい%しん}}: [[cinnamon]] or [[cassia]] bark, as used in cooking; {{taxlink|Cinnamomum tenuifolium|species|noshow=1}}, Japanese cinnamon; a type of [[mochi]] [[confection]] coated in cinnamon [[powder]]
* {{ja-r|桂%仙%花|けい%せん%か}}: alternate word for {{m|ja|翁草|tr=okinagusa}}, {{taxlink|Pulsatilla cernua|species|noshow=1}}, a type of low-growing [[anemone]]
